At 17:30 yesterday (12 March) , a China Eastern Airlines A350-900 took off from Shanghai Pudong International Airport on a charter flight MU787, carrying a group of nine people and about nine tons of supplies from the Chinese government and the Red Cross Society of China to Italy, from Shanghai to Rome. Three hours to complete flight clearance

At about 9:00 p.m. on March 11, a mission order for urgent transportation of Chinese experts to Italy and a chartered flight of epidemic prevention materials was sent from the Civil Aviation Administration to China Eastern Airlines. Since the outbreak has carried out a number of domestic and foreign anti-epidemic charter mission of China Eastern Airlines, immediately launched a response, held overnight preparations for action.

"At present, china-italy routes have been temporarily suspended, so charter flights must obtain local permission to take off and land, " said Peng Haiyan, deputy director of China Eastern's National Defense Mobilization Office. After the headquarters of China Eastern Airlines Operation Control and other departments in close cooperation with the Rome local business department, and finally just after midnight on China Standard Time, the Italian side of the charter was approved.

The nine members of the expert group sent by China to Italy are from the National Health and Health Commission, the Red Cross Society of China, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the Sichuan Red Cross, the Sichuan Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the Sichuan University and the Hwaseo Hospital, have been fighting in the front of the civil war "epidemic" , has the new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control and treatment of rich experience, some experts have also experienced the Wenchuan County earthquake, aid Ebola epidemic areas in west Africa and many other major tests.
